This paper deals with the analysis of security protocols in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of constraint solvers to automatically analyze protocols suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with the transmission and processing of information in wireless networks, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with the behavior of nodes in a network, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the classification of scenarios in which protocols can operate, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
